        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/15447",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=bkarwin",
                        "name": "bkarwin",
                        "displayName": "Bill Karwin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I see no justification for this change.  Can you explain why it's more convenient to do this:\n\n{code}\n$log = new Zend_Log(...);\n$log->addWriter(...)\n    ->info(...);\n{code}\n\nInstead of this:\n\n{code}\n$log = new Zend_Log(...);\n$log->addWriter(...);\n$log->info(...);\n{code}\n\nEspecially since in typical usage, the call to addWriter() and the call to info() are not close together in one's application.  Typically, logs are set up in the bootstrap, and then messages are output in many places in the code.  \n\nAnother use case is where one might want to output to multiple log levels when a single log event occurs in the app:\n\n{code}\n$log->info( ...some short message... );\n$log->debug( ...some longer message... );\n{code}\n\nIs it really so painful to write {{$log}} twice in such cases?  I don't think so.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=bkarwin",
                        "name": "bkarwin",
                        "displayName": "Bill Karwin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-06-25T14:07:38.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-06-25T14:07:38.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/15449",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=potatobob",
                        "name": "potatobob",
                        "displayName": "Geoffrey Tran",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "It is for cases where several filters or writers are added not for chaining log events after Zend_Log instantiation because as you said logs are typically setup in the bootstrap.\n\n{code}\n$log = new Zend_Log(...);\n$log->addWriter(...)\n        ->addFilter($filter)\n        ->addFilter($filter2);\n{code}\n\nOf course it does not matter whether we have to hit a few extra keys, but it does make things easier by shaving off 0.5 seconds when setting up Zend_Log.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=potatobob",
                        "name": "potatobob",
                        "displayName": "Geoffrey Tran",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-06-25T20:17:44.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-06-25T20:17:44.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/15450",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=bkarwin",
                        "name": "bkarwin",
                        "displayName": "Bill Karwin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I think optimizing keystrokes is not really the intended value of fluent interfaces.\nAnd returning {{$this}} does not a fluent interface make.\n\nI had a discussion with the designer of this component, and he said he didn't implement the function to return {{$this}} because the design of this API is not designed to be a true fluent interface according to the Martin Fowler pattern.  In fact, most of the instances of functions that return {{$this}} in Zend Framework aren't proper fluent interfaces.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=bkarwin",
                        "name": "bkarwin",
                        "displayName": "Bill Karwin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-06-25T23:41:38.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-06-25T23:41:38.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/15462",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=bkarwin",
                        "name": "bkarwin",
                        "displayName": "Bill Karwin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I'm sorry, but the use case for this feature request is not convincing.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=bkarwin",
                        "name": "bkarwin",
                        "displayName": "Bill Karwin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-06-26T11:19:15.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-06-26T11:19:15.000+0000"
                }
            ]
        }
    },
